Body: The processMatches function now requires animateMerges and animateUnblocking to be provided for the matches to be actually processed. If called without these parameters, the matched tiles won't be cleared and merged tiles won't be created. While the current code always provides these functions through game.processMatches(), this API design is error-prone. Consider either: (1) calling processMerges directly when animations are not provided, or (2) making the animations required parameters instead of optional with defaults.

