File: src/input-handler.js:513
Body: The executeSwap function checks tile1 and tile2 for hasBeenSwapped property before tiles are swapped, but then marks them as swapped after the swap. This means the checks on lines 471-480 are using the original positions, but the assignments on lines 508-512 are using the swapped positions (row2/col2 for tile1, row1/col1 for tile2). This is correct, but could be confusing. Consider adding a comment explaining that the hasBeenSwapped checks use pre-swap positions while the assignments use post-swap positions.

