Body: The change to remove tiles from board state BEFORE triggering animations (lines 200-208, 254-255, 281-284, 301-326) is a significant timing change. This means that if any code reads from game.board during the animation period, it will see tiles as already removed. Verify that no animation callbacks or async operations depend on reading the board state during the animation window, as this could lead to race conditions or incorrect behavior.

